## Routing — When to Read This File

| Trigger | Why |
|---------|-----|
| SSH, VPS, hosting | Server address, SSH key, access method |
| Docker, docker-compose, container | Paths, services, restart policy |
| Secret, API key, credential | Canonical $ENV_VAR name (value in .env) |
| Service principal, app registration | AppId, cert, roles, expiry |
| MCP configure or debug | Endpoint, auth type, limit param |
| systemd, background service | Status commands, known gotchas |
| External API integration | Base URL, auth, rate limits |
| Deploy, CI/CD | Server + Docker + secrets combined |

---

## Update Rules — Write in Same Commit as Infra Change

| Event | Section to update |
|-------|-------------------|
| New secret created | Secrets table → add row ($ENV_VAR_NAME) |
| Service account created or cert renewed | Service Principals → ID, auth, expiry, roles |
| New MCP added | MCP Servers + .claude/rules/tool-routing.md |
| Docker service added/modified | Docker Services |
| API key changed/rotated | Update $ENV_VAR reference — NEVER the value |
| New external API integrated | External APIs → add section |
| New server/VPS provisioned | Servers & Hosting |
| Background service added | Systemd / Background Services |

---

## Staleness Detection

If a secret name, AppId, endpoint, or service in this file doesn't match reality
(actual KV / secrets manager / Entra / cloud console) → this file is stale.
**Fix before any work that depends on it.**

